		{
			"name": "WebSocket Events (Reference)",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "WebSocket Connection Info",
					"request": {
						"method": "GET",
						"header": [],
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{url}}/chat",
							"host": [
								"{{url}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"chat"
							]
						},
						"description": "WebSocket connection reference:\n\n**Connection URL:**\n```\nws://localhost:7000/chat?userId={chatUserId}&userRole={ADMIN|DOCTOR}\n```\n\n**Client Events (Emit):**\n- `join_conversation`: { conversationId }\n- `send_message`: { conversationId, message, imageUrl? }\n- `typing`: { conversationId, isTyping }\n- `mark_as_read`: { conversationId }\n- `user_online`: { userId }\n- `user_offline`: { userId }\n\n**Server Events (Listen):**\n- `new_message`: { message }\n- `user_typing`: { userId, isTyping }\n- `messages_read`: { conversationId, userId }\n- `unread_count`: { count }\n- `user_online`: { userId }\n- `user_offline`: { userId }\n\n**Example (JavaScript):**\n```javascript\nconst socket = io('http://localhost:7000/chat', {\n  query: {\n    userId: 'chat-user-id',\n    userRole: 'DOCTOR'\n  }\n});\n\nsocket.emit('join_conversation', { conversationId: 'conv-id' }, (response) => {\n  console.log(response.conversation.messages);\n});\n\nsocket.emit('send_message', {\n  conversationId: 'conv-id',\n  message: 'Hello!',\n  imageUrl: 'optional-file-url'\n});\n\nsocket.on('new_message', (data) => {\n  console.log('New message:', data.message);\n});\n```"
					},
					"response": []
				}
			],
			"description": "WebSocket event reference (not executable in Postman, use Socket.IO client)"
		}
